<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="824" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d824">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/12525.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Brazilian Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-17">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 17, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>88. The whole diplomatic corps attended today the official reception of
                            Provisional President; Spanish Minister as Dean of Corps made usual
                            address. The President in his reply confirmed his good intentions to
                            promote the pacification of country and frankly added that his person
                            would in no way be an obstacle to it.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Cardoso de Oliveira</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
